<!--
  SHELVED variant (ADR 0012's preferred experiment) - NOT wired into the
  build. This is the no-JIT-entitlement posture that pairs with spawning
  the sidecar with V8's jitless flag. (XML comments cannot contain a
  double hyphen, so the flag is spelled without its dashes here.)

  Verified 2026-07-11 on Node v24.14.0/darwin-arm64: jitless disables
  WebAssembly ("WebAssembly is not defined"), and Node's global fetch()
  (undici) parses HTTP with WASM llhttp - so every fetch() fails, the
  Ollama availability probe returns false, and Tier-2 redaction silently
  degrades (invariant 6 violation). Vault crypto (sodium-native) and
  SQLite were unaffected - the addons are native, not JIT-dependent.

  To revive this posture, packages/librarian's Ollama client (and any
  other fetch() caller) would have to move to node:http first. Until
  then, point bundle.macOS.entitlements at entitlements.plist (allow-jit).
-->
